bug.short_desc: JVM crash in ClassVerifier::verify_invoke_init() when activating task with CDT package

long_desc.thetext:
Steps: 1. Download Kepler M7 CDT package 2. Activate task
This causes Eclipse to crash. This is reproducible with various Java 6 and 7 versions on Linux and Windows.
Created attachment 230832 crash 1
Created attachment 230833 crash 2
My suspicion is that this is related to the code in the bundle. I can't reproduce it if I export the bundle from my workspace so it could be related to signing, packing or building with Tycho.
The problem doesn't occur if I build Mylyn Context locally. I'm runnin another weekly build to verify if this is a specific problem with the last build.
Did you get a chance to test this build?
It didn't work for me. The same crash happened when I activated the task.

When I activate a task, immediately before the crash, the following exception is logged:
org.eclipse.core.runtime.AssertionFailedException: assertion failed: at org.eclipse.core.runtime.Assert.isTrue(Assert.java:110) at org.eclipse.core.runtime.Assert.isTrue(Assert.java:96) at org.eclipse.ui.internal.WorkbenchPage.openEditors(WorkbenchPage.java:4316) at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method) at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(Unknown Source) at sun.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(Unknown Source) at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Unknown Source) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.context.ui.state.EditorStateParticipant.restoreEditors_e_3_8_2(EditorStateParticipant.java:416) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.context.ui.state.EditorStateParticipant.restoreEditors(EditorStateParticipant.java:367) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.context.ui.state.EditorStateParticipant.restoreState(EditorStateParticipant.java:128) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.context.ui.state.ContextStateManager$3.run(ContextStateManager.java:114) at org.eclipse.mylyn.internal.context.ui.state.ContextStateManager$3.run(ContextStateManager.java:1) at org.eclipse.mylyn.commons.core.CommonListenerList$1.run(CommonListenerList.java:93)
Well, this happens even when there is no crash.

If I edit the plugin.xml in the jar to remove the CDTContextLabelProvider, the crash doesn't happen. If I replace the CDTContextLabelProvider.class file with one I compiled myself, the crash doesn't happen. If I copy the class file from the jar into my workspace and bootstrap on it, the crash happens. So it is definitely something wrong with the class file.
I have tested https://hudson.eclipse.org/hudson/view/Mylyn/job/mylyn-3.9.x-release/23/console and the crash still happens.
Have you tried the nightly? The only difference is that it's not signed: http://download.eclipse.org/mylyn/snapshots/nightly/reviews/.

I see this as well on Windows 7, JRE7. I can reproduce 100% of the time by activating a local task.
I am using kepler-rc1. This occurs out of the box with the 64bit Win7 CDT Eclipse distribution, but I've also tried the latest from the following Mylyn and CDT update sites:
http://download.eclipse.org/tools/cdt/builds/kepler/nightly http://download.eclipse.org/mylyn/snapshots/kepler

Created attachment 231728 crash 3
Crash log

Updating to the nightly for Mylyn Context resolved this for me: http://download.eclipse.org/mylyn/snapshots/nightly/
Mylyn Context Connector: C/C++ Development 5.5.0.I20130529-1422 org.eclipse.cdt.mylyn.feature.group Eclipse Mylyn Mylyn Context Connector: Eclipse IDE 3.9.0.I20130529-1422 org.eclipse.mylyn.ide_feature.feature.group Eclipse Mylyn Mylyn Context Connector: Java Development 3.9.0.I20130529-1422 org.eclipse.mylyn.java_feature.feature.group Eclipse Mylyn Mylyn Context Connector: Plug-in Development 3.9.0.I20130529-1422 org.eclipse.mylyn.pde_feature.feature.group Eclipse Mylyn Mylyn Context Connector: Team Support 3.9.0.I20130529-1422 org.eclipse.mylyn.team_feature.feature.group Eclipse Mylyn
Thanks for trying that out. That suggests that the signing is corrupting the class file.

I have tried installing unpacked jars (http://download.eclipse.org/mylyn/drops/3.9.0/I20130529-1332/mylyn-3.9.0.I20130529-1332.zip) but the crash still happens. By dropping the broken class file into my workspace, I am able to get the crash when debugging. It happens on line 184 of RegistryStrategyOSGI when it calls @classInstance.newInstance()@ on the CDTContextLabelProvider class, as soon as I try to step into the method.

The crash also happens if I explicitly call the CDTContextLabelProvider constructor, call @CDTContextLabelProvider.createCDTUiLabelProvider@ or even just do @CDTContextLabelProvider.class.getMethods().@
Steffen, I've pushed a review with some simple refactoring of the class to https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/13606/. Can we trigger a build from the review to see if this prevents the corruption from happening? I am running out of ideas.
If I understand correctly, it seems like this is caused by the signing and not the packaging. Is there anything else we can do about it?

(In reply to comment #17) > Steffen, I've pushed a review with some simple refactoring of the class to > https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/13606/. Can we trigger a build from the review to > see if this prevents the corruption from happening? I am running out of ideas.
The latest build should include the change.
> If I understand correctly, it seems like this is caused by the signing and not > the packaging. Is there anything else we can do about it?
It sounds like it happens somewhere in that signing process. I'm not sure why class files would get mangled at all but that would be something worth investigating.

The latest weekly still causes JVM crashes. I'm proposing that we remove the label provider as a stop gap solution: https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/13627/. It's only relevant for the incubator so this change isn't going to have an impact for the vast majority of users.
Removing the class did the trick for me. The crash no longer occurred when activating/deactivating a task with the latest weekly build installed into the Kepler CPP package.

Great! Thanks a lot for testing this, Steffen. I've created the following bug to follow up:
410223: investigate JVM crash when instantiating signed CDTContextLabelProvider https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=410223
